{"lemma":"فَصُّ","slug":"فَصُّ","root":"ف.ص.ص","root_slug":"ف-ص-ص","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ص-ص","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33954","n33955","n33956"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a roundish object that is apparently or actually attached to or separable from another object; a circular, dome-shaped, or spherical object set into another (like the stone of a ring, the bead of an earring, or the pupil of the eye)","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"كَانَ خَاتَمُ النَّبِيِّ مِنْ فِضَّةٍ وَفَصُّهُ مِنْهُ.","english":"The ring of the Prophet was of silver, and its stone was of it [likewise]."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a roundish object that is apparently or actually attached to or separable from another object; the core, kernel, or nucleus of a proposition or idea","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a roundish object of many forming a composite whole; a semicircular division of a fruit (as in citrus fruits, like mandarins or oranges), a segment","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a roundish object of many forming a composite whole; a semicircular bulb (as in garlic), a clove","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a roundish object of many forming a composite whole; a gross anatomical division or extension of an organ (as of a brain, a liver, or a kidney), a lobe","tags":["countable"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fasˤsˤ/","/fusˤsˤ/","/fisˤsˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33954","headword_ar":"فَصٌّ","root":"fS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", of a ring, or signet, (S, M, A, Msb, K,) signifies [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gem,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is set"},{"kind":"text","text":"therein, (Lth, M, L, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a different substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"therefrom; (Msb;) and is also written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiS~N","text_ar":"فِصٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K,) thus pronounced by the vulgar, (Lth, S,) but J's saying this does not necessarily mean that it is incorrect, which, as in opposition to what is said by J, it is asserted not to be in the K [and A], (TA,) or the latter form is bad, accord. to ISk and El-Fárábee; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuS~N","text_ar":"فُصٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) all of which three forms are mentioned by Ibn-Málik and others; but they assert that the first is the most correct and the most commonly known: (TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afuS~N","text_ar":"اَفُصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, M) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSuwSN","text_ar":"فُصُوصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiSaASN","text_ar":"فِصَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, M.) ―         -b2-  [Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any gem,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar stone, rare"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"factitious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any hard stone cut for inlaying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for construction."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A die, such as is used in the game of tables,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"backgammon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ossicle that is used in like manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaEobN","text_ar":"كَعْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A clove"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~N","text_ar":"سِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") of garlic; (Lth, A, O, K;) [and] so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faS~apN","text_ar":"فَصَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S and L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sn","text_ar":"سن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yolk"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an egg. (M, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muH~N","text_ar":"مُحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bubbles"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water. (M.) ―         -b7-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What leaps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leap, up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particles that leap up, in effervescence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of wine. (M.) ―         -b8-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadaqap","text_ar":"حَدَقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") of the eye: (M, K:) [or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pupil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earafotu AlbagoDaA='a fiY faS~i Hadaqatihi","text_ar":"عَرَفْتُ البَغْضَا=ءَ فِى فَصِّ حَدَقَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I knew vehement hatred in the pupil of the black of his eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramawohu bifuSuwSi A^aEoyunihimo","text_ar":"رَمَوْهُ بِفُصُوصِ اَعْيُنِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they cast piercing glances at him with their eyeballs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b9-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A joint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of separation between two parts of an animal:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any joint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any place of meeting of two bones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fingers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, M,) for the joints thereof are not so called: (M:) pl., in this and all the other senses which we have mentioned, [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afuS~N","text_ar":"اَفُصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSuwSN","text_ar":"فُصُوصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, A, Msb:) or, as some say, contradicting AZ, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fSwS","text_ar":"فصوص"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAjim","text_ar":"بَرَاجِم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulaAmayaAt","text_ar":"سُلَامَيَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": [see these two words:] (Sh, TA:) and ISh says, in the “ Book of Horses, ” that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fSwS","text_ar":"فصوص"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse are the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joints of the knee and pasterns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which latter are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulaAmayaAt","text_ar":"سُلَامَيَات"},{"kind":"text","text":", these being the bones of the pasterns. (TA.) One says of a horse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a fuSuwSahu laZimaA='N","text_ar":"اـِنَّ فُصُوصَهُ لَظِمَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily his joints are hard; not flabby nor fleshy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) [And hence, app., from the place in which it is mentioned by Z in this art., the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Haz~aAzu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ حَزَّازُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuSuwSi","text_ar":"الفُصُوصِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in a copy of the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haz~aAru","text_ar":"حَزَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DrAr","text_ar":"ضرار"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but I have no doubt that the right reading is that which I have given; lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the great cutter of joints;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is often right in his judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion, and in his answer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b10-  Hence, [immediately,] accord. to Abu-l-'Abbás; or [originally] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faS~N","text_ar":"فَصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first of the senses expl. above, accord. to IDrd; (Mtr, cited in De Sacy's Chrest. Arabe, see. ed. iii. 232;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faS~u A^amorK","text_ar":"فَصُّ اَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The point upon which a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affair, turns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinges;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the point in which it is distinguished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discriminated, from other things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoSiluhu","text_ar":"مَفْصِلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Abu-l- 'Abbás ubi suprà, S, Msb, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaz~uhN","text_ar":"مَحَزُّهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mtr ubi suprá:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its utmost point,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particular;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munotahaAhu","text_ar":"مُنْتَهَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fSl","text_ar":"فصل"},{"kind":"text","text":", in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoSilu A^morK","text_ar":"مَفْصِلُ امْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its origin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"source;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoluh","text_ar":"اَصْلُه"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M; and Mtr ubi suprà, and L;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxorajuhu","text_ar":"مَخْرَجُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*Y qado xaraja minohu","text_ar":"الَّذى قَدْ خَرَجَ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its essence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very essence; its substance; its most essential,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elementary, part; its pith; the ultimate element to which it can be reduced"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resolved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haqiyqatuhu","text_ar":"حَقِيقَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunohuhu","text_ar":"كُنْهُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawoharuhu","text_ar":"جَوْهَرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nihaAyatuhu","text_ar":"نِهَايَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its real, as opposed to its apparent, state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobaruhu","text_ar":"مَخْبَرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) Hence the saying, (S, Msb, TA,) of a poet, (S, TA,) or of Ez-Zubeyr Ibn-El-'Owwám, (TA,) or of 'AbdAllah Ibn-Jaafar Ibn-Abee-Tálib, (Mtr ubi suprà, and TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wayaA^otiyka biAlA^amori mino faS~ihi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he will tell thee the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"tracing it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the point on which it turns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinges;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: but it appears to be originally without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; forming an incomplete hemistich: see Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 918]: (S, M, * A, * Mtr, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he will tell thee the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair, distinctly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA. *) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^otu fiY faS~i AlkitaAbi ka*aA","text_ar":"قَرَاْتُ فِى فَصِّ الكِتَابِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I read, in the most essential part of the book"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing, such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSuwSu","text_ar":"فُصُوصُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axobaAri","text_ar":"الاَخْبَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most essential parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particulars of narrations"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K","Lth","L","TA","AZ","ISk","Sh"]},{"entry_id":"n33955","headword_ar":"فُصٌّ","root":"fS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faS~N","text_ar":"فَصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first signification."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33956","headword_ar":"فِصٌّ","root":"fS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faS~N","text_ar":"فَصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first signification."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}